[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":1599},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2023\u002F03\u002F30\u002Fimporting-images-in-vue\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2023\u002F03\u002F30\u002Fimporting-images-in-vue\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2023\u002F03\u002F30\u002Fimporting-images-in-vue\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2023\u002F03\u002F30\u002Fimporting-images-in-vue\u002F":1576,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2023\u002F03\u002F30\u002Fimporting-images-in-vue\u002F":1585},"\u002Fvue\u002F20230330\u002F238425903\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":1558,"date":1559,"description":19,"extension":1560,"lang":1561,"meta":1562,"navigation":471,"path":1563,"readingMinutes":1564,"seo":1565,"standalone":1566,"stem":1567,"tags":1568,"tldr":1573,"updated":1559,"url":1574,"__hash__":1575},"content\u002Fen\u002FVue\u002Fimporting-images-in-vue.md","How to Import Images in Vue (Vue CLI and Vite)","2985243003",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":1540},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,30,33,43,56,100,111,118,139,142,168,171,197,200,204,210,234,240,243,286,289,319,329,332,336,339,356,361,371,619,637,668,671,675,680,706,709,713,716,742,745,803,809,816,842,845,869,873,884,901,908,934,940,966,974,986,990,993,1007,1011,1018,1131,1135,1138,1214,1218,1221,1235,1240,1316,1321,1397,1401,1411,1414,1420,1479,1482,1536],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"A quick note on how to import images properly in Vue CLI or Vite. It's a common question and easy to get wrong, so I figured I'd write it down.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"static-vs-non-static-assets","Static vs non-static assets",[17,25,26],{},"Before getting into the how, I want to explain what \"static\" and \"non-static\" assets actually mean.",[17,28,29],{},"Since I'll be talking about Vue CLI later, let me use Vue CLI as the example here.",[17,31,32],{},"Vue CLI is built on Webpack, so importing images breaks down into two categories:",[34,35,36,40],"ul",{},[37,38,39],"li",{},"Static assets",[37,41,42],{},"Non-static assets",[17,44,45,46,50,51,55],{},"What's a static asset? Remember the ",[47,48,49],"code",{},"public"," folder in a Vue CLI project? That folder is specifically for static assets — and by \"static\" I mean ",[52,53,54],"strong",{},"assets that don't go through Webpack bundling\u002Fcompilation",". So you can reference them directly in HTML:",[57,58,63],"pre",{"className":59,"code":60,"language":61,"meta":62,"style":62},"language-html shiki shiki-themes github-light github-light github-dark-high-contrast","\u003Cimg src=\"\u002Fimg\u002Flogo.png\" alt=\"logo\" \u002F>\n","html","",[47,64,65],{"__ignoreMap":62},[66,67,70,74,78,82,85,89,92,94,97],"span",{"class":68,"line":69},"line",1,[66,71,73],{"class":72},"s8XSl","\u003C",[66,75,77],{"class":76},"syv7_","img",[66,79,81],{"class":80},"sK3KL"," src",[66,83,84],{"class":72},"=",[66,86,88],{"class":87},"sWayO","\"\u002Fimg\u002Flogo.png\"",[66,90,91],{"class":80}," alt",[66,93,84],{"class":72},[66,95,96],{"class":87},"\"logo\"",[66,98,99],{"class":72}," \u002F>\n",[17,101,102,103,106,107,110],{},"And your ",[47,104,105],{},"logo.png"," would live at ",[47,108,109],{},"public\u002Fimg\u002Flogo.png",".",[17,112,113,114,117],{},"Non-static assets, on the other hand, are bundled\u002Fcompiled by Webpack, so you have to bring them in via ",[47,115,116],{},"import",":",[57,119,123],{"className":120,"code":121,"language":122,"meta":62,"style":62},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-light github-light github-dark-high-contrast","import logo from '.\u002Fimg\u002Flogo.png'\n","js",[47,124,125],{"__ignoreMap":62},[66,126,127,130,133,136],{"class":68,"line":69},[66,128,116],{"class":129},"sOudu",[66,131,132],{"class":72}," logo ",[66,134,135],{"class":129},"from",[66,137,138],{"class":87}," '.\u002Fimg\u002Flogo.png'\n",[17,140,141],{},"Then in your HTML you'd use:",[57,143,145],{"className":59,"code":144,"language":61,"meta":62,"style":62},"\u003Cimg :src=\"logo\" a